<paragraph blockId="9.[151,557,402,428]" box="[151,557,402,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,557,402,428]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,557,402,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Malloch, 1909" authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1909" box="[238,557,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Spiniphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,374,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Spiniphora</emphasis>
Malloch, 
<number box="[498,557,402,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="1909.0">1909</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,473,642]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
This is a relatively small genus with about 
<number box="[638,666,473,497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="20.0">20</number>
species from the Palaearctic, Nearctic and Oriental regions. Only 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz, 1935" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Spiniphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">S. signata</emphasis>
Schmitz, 
<number box="[347,403,509,534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="1935.0">1935</number>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[722,784,509,534]" name="Israel" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[799,1109,509,534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Nussbaum, Y. (1990) Phoridae (Diptera) from Israel. Israel Journal of Entomology, 24, 107 - 114." type="journal article" year="1990">
Disney &amp; Nussbaum, 
<number box="[1049,1109,510,534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lengyel" box="[1121,1298,509,534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" refString="Lengyel, G. D. (2011 a) The first Rhynchomicropteron Annandale, 1912 (Diptera, Phoridae) species from the Palearctic region, with taxonomic and faunistic notes on the fauna of Israel. Zootaxa, 2885, 23 - 32." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="a">
Lengyel, 
<number box="[1227,1285,510,534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), being now known from both the coastal plain and Judean hills. Another species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mik, 1864" authorityName="Mik" authorityYear="1864" box="[922,1248,545,570]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Spiniphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergenstammi">
<emphasis box="[922,1106,545,570]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">S. bergenstammi</emphasis>
(Mik, 
<number box="[1182,1240,545,570]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="1864.0">1864</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
was erroneously indicated for the 
<collectingCountry box="[344,414,581,606]" name="Israel" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Israeli</collectingCountry>
fauna by 
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[528,848,581,606]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Nussbaum, Y. (1990) Phoridae (Diptera) from Israel. Israel Journal of Entomology, 24, 107 - 114." type="journal article" year="1990">
Disney &amp; Nussbaum (
<number box="[780,840,582,606]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, being collected in Sidon, 
<collectingCountry box="[1151,1253,581,606]" name="Lebanon" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
. However, quite expectedly this Holarctic species is present in 
<collectingCountry box="[668,730,617,642]" name="Israel" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Israel</collectingCountry>
as well.
</paragraph>
